## 🔴 Critical Performance Issues

### 1. `has_legal_moves()` — O(64²) Legal Move Generation with Full Board Copy Per Call

```c
// CURRENT: 4096 iterations, each doing a full BoardState copy + attack scan
int has_legal_moves(const BoardState *state) {
    for (int f = 0; f < 64; f++) {
        if (state->board[f] == 0) continue;
        if ((state->turn == 1 && state->board[f] < 0) || ...) continue;
        for (int t = 0; t < 64; t++) {
            GuiMove m = {f, t, 0};
            if (is_legal_gui_move(state, m)) return 1;  // BoardState copy every call!
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```

**Problem:** `is_legal_gui_move` calls `make_gui_move` which copies the entire `BoardState` struct (64 ints + metadata = ~272 bytes) on every iteration. In the worst case, this is **4096 struct copies** before returning. This is called every frame via `update_gui_cache()`.

```c
// OPTIMIZED: Early-exit piece iteration + skip impossible targets
int has_legal_moves(const BoardState *state) {
    // Pre-collect own piece squares to avoid scanning empty squares twice
    int own_pieces[16];
    int own_count = 0;
    
    for (int f = 0; f < 64 && own_count < 16; f++) {
        int p = state->board[f];
        if (p == 0) continue;
        if (state->turn == 1 ? p > 0 : p < 0) {
            own_pieces[own_count++] = f;
        }
    }
    
    for (int pi = 0; pi < own_count; pi++) {
        int f = own_pieces[pi];
        int abs_p = abs(state->board[f]);
        
        for (int t = 0; t < 64; t++) {
            // Skip squares occupied by own pieces before making a copy
            int tgt = state->board[t];
            if (tgt != 0 && (state->turn == 1 ? tgt > 0 : tgt < 0)) continue;
            
            GuiMove m = {f, t, 0};
            if (abs_p == 1 && (t / 8 == 0 || t / 8 == 7)) m.promo = 5;
            if (is_legal_gui_move(state, m)) return 1;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```

**Further optimization** — make `make_gui_move` avoid a full copy using a delta approach:

```c
// Store only the deltas needed to verify legality, avoid full struct copy
int is_legal_gui_move_nocopy(const BoardState *state, GuiMove m) {
    if (!is_pseudo_legal_move(state, m)) return 0;
    
    // Inline the minimum state changes needed for king-safety check
    // instead of copying the whole BoardState
    int saved_from = state->board[m.from];
    int saved_to   = state->board[m.to];
    int saved_ep_cap = 0;
    int ep_cap_sq = -1;
    
    // Cast away const for temporary mutation (restore immediately after)
    BoardState *s = (BoardState *)state;
    
    s->board[m.from] = 0;
    s->board[m.to]   = (m.promo != 0) ? state->turn * m.promo : saved_from;
    
    // Handle en-passant capture square
    if (abs(saved_from) == 1 && m.to == state->ep) {
        ep_cap_sq    = m.to + (state->turn == 1 ? 8 : -8);
        saved_ep_cap = s->board[ep_cap_sq];
        s->board[ep_cap_sq] = 0;
    }
    
    int king = find_king(s, state->turn);
    int legal = (king != -1) && !is_square_attacked(s, king, -state->turn);
    
    // Restore state
    s->board[m.from] = saved_from;
    s->board[m.to]   = saved_to;
    if (ep_cap_sq != -1) s->board[ep_cap_sq] = saved_ep_cap;
    
    return legal;
}
```

> ⚠️ This mutation+restore pattern is valid **only** if the GUI runs single-threaded during move validation (which it does — the engine runs on a separate KThread).

