## 🟡 Moderate Issues

### 7. `draw_ui()` — Excessive `printf` Calls (ANSI Escape Sequences)

The Wii's `console_init` framebuffer console processes each `printf` call synchronously. Currently `draw_ui()` makes **50+ individual printf calls** per frame.

```c
// OPTIMIZED: Build entire frame into a single buffer, one fwrite call
void draw_ui() {
    static char frame_buf[8192];
    int pos = 0;
    
    #define FB_APPEND(str) do { \
        int _l = strlen(str); \
        if (pos + _l < (int)sizeof(frame_buf) - 1) { \
            memcpy(frame_buf + pos, str, _l); \
            pos += _l; \
        } \
    } while(0)
    
    #define FB_PRINTF(fmt, ...) do { \
        pos += snprintf(frame_buf + pos, sizeof(frame_buf) - pos, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__); \
    } while(0)
    
    FB_PRINTF("\033[H\r\n");
    // ... build entire frame ...
    
    fwrite(frame_buf, 1, pos, stdout);
    fflush(stdout);
}
```

