## 🟢 Minor / Platform-Specific Issues

### 11. Division/Modulo in Hot Loops — Replace with Bitwise ops

The Wii's Broadway CPU (PPC 750CL) has **no hardware integer divide instruction**. All `/` and `%` operations are software-emulated and take **~20 cycles** each.

```c
// EXPENSIVE on Broadway PPC:
int r = sq / 8;   // ~20 cycles
int c = sq % 8;   // ~20 cycles

// FREE on PPC (single-cycle shift/AND):
int r = sq >> 3;   // 1 cycle
int c = sq & 7;    // 1 cycle
```

Apply throughout `is_square_attacked()`, `is_pseudo_legal_move()`, `update_selected_dests_cache()`, and `draw_ui()`:

```c
// Before:
int fr = m.from / 8, fc = m.from % 8;
int tr = m.to   / 8, tc = m.to   % 8;

// After:
int fr = m.from >> 3, fc = m.from & 7;
int tr = m.to   >> 3, tc = m.to   & 7;
```

