### 13. `BoardState` Alignment for `memcmp`/`memcpy`

The Broadway CPU prefers 32-byte aligned data for cache line operations:

```c
// Add alignment attribute:
typedef struct __attribute__((aligned(32))) {
    int board[64];
    int turn;
    int castle;
    int ep;
    int halfmoves;
    int fullmoves;
} BoardState;
```

This ensures `memcmp` in `count_repetitions` and `memcpy` in `make_gui_move` operate on cache-line-aligned data, avoiding split cache line penalties.

